                <h1>Understanding the Endocrine System: Hormones & Health</h1>
                <p>The endocrine system is a network of glands that produce and release hormones, regulating various bodily functions such as metabolism, growth, and mood. Key components include the pituitary, thyroid, adrenal glands, and pancreas. Hormones act as messengers, influencing processes throughout the body for homeostasis and overall health.</p>
